To understand the tools you use, you have to understand the problem.

Without knowing that a pencil needs to be sharpened you can't understand how a knife might come in handy.
Having never seen a pencil, it's tough to articulate the difference between a knife and an electric pencil sharpener.

That's why Rails is a bad first framework.
I love Rails, but I wish I had started with something else.
Something closer to the metal, that brings you face to face with the problems frameworks try to solve.
